#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:208 index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Memory Information Module"
msgstr "Informacioni modul memorije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This module displays the current memory usage. It is updated constantly, and "
"can be very useful for pinpointing bottlenecks when certain applications are "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj modul prikazuje trenutnu iskorišćenost memorije. Neprekidno se ažurira, "
"te može pomoći utvrđivanju uskih grla u radu izvesnih programa."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "Memory Types"
msgstr "Tipovi memorije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first thing you must understand, is there are two types of "
"<quote>memory</quote>, available to the operating system and the programs "
"that run within it."
msgstr ""
"Prva treba da uočite da postoje dva tipa „memorije“, dostupna operativnom "
"sistemu i programima koji se izvršavaju pod njim."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first type, is called physical memory. This is the memory located within "
"the memory chips, within your computer. This is the <acronym>RAM</acronym> "
"(for Random Access Memory) you bought when you purchased your computer."
msgstr ""
"Prvi tip je <emphasis>fizička</emphasis> memorija. Ovo je memorija smeštena "
"u memorijskim čipovima u računaru, RAM (engl. skr. „nasumično pristupna "
"memorija“) koji ste kupili zajedno sa računarom."

# skip-rule: t-space
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second type of memory, is called virtual or swap memory. This block of "
"memory, is actually space on the hard drive. The operating system reserves a "
"space on the hard drive for <quote>swap space</quote>. The operating system "
"can use this virtual memory (or swap space), if it runs out of physical "
"memory. The reason this is called <quote>swap</quote> memory, is the "
"operating system takes some data that it doesn't think you will want for a "
"while, and saves that to disk in this reserved space. The operating system "
"then loads the new data you need right now. It has <quote>swapped</quote> "
"the not needed data, for the data you need right now. Virtual or swap memory "
"is not as fast as physical memory, so operating systems try to keep data "
"(especially often used data), in the physical memory."
msgstr ""
"Drugi tip memorije jeste virtuelna ili <emphasis>razmenska</emphasis> "
"memorija. Ovaj memorijski blok zapravo je prostor na hard‑disku, koji "
"operativni sistem rezerviše kao „razmenu“. Operativni sistem može upotrebiti "
"ovu virtuelnu memoriju, ili razmenu, kad potroši fizičku memoriju. Ova "
"memorija naziva se razmenskom zato što operativni sistem u nju, tj. na disk, "
"upisuje neke podatke za koje proceni da vam neće trebati neko vreme, a zatim "
"učitava nove podatke su vam potrebni odmah. Time je „razmenio“ trenutno "
"nepotrebne podatke sa onim odmah potrebnim. Virtuelna, ili razmenska "
"memorija, mnogo je sporija od fizičke, te operativni sistem pokušava da drži "
"podatke (naročito često korišćene) u fizičkoj memoriji."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The total memory, is the combined total of physical memory and virtual "
"memory."
msgstr "Ukupna memorija je zbir ukupne fizičke i razmenske memorije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid "This window is divided into a top and bottom section"
msgstr "Ovaj prozor podeljen je na gornju i donju sekciju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The top section shows you the total physical memory, total free physical "
"memory, shared memory, and buffered memory."
msgstr ""
"Gornja sekcija pokazuje ukupnu fizičku, ukupnu slobodnu fizičku, deljenu i "
"bafersku memoriju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All four values are represented as the total number of bytes, and as the "
"number of megabytes (1 megabyte = slightly more than 1,000,000 bytes)"
msgstr ""
"Sve četiri vrednosti predstavljene su ukupnim brojem bajtova i kao broj "
"megabajta (1 megabajt je nešto malo više od 1.000.000 bajtova);"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "The bottom section shows you three graphs:"
msgstr "Donja sekcija sadrži tri grafikona:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Total Memory</guilabel> (this is the combination of physical and "
"virtual memory)."
msgstr "ukupna memorija (kombinacija fizičke i virtuelne memorije);"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "Physical Memory"
msgstr "fizička memorija;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:261
#, no-c-format
msgid "Virtual memory, or <guilabel>Swap Space</guilabel>."
msgstr "virtuelna memorija, ili razmena."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid "The grey areas are free, and the blue and green areas are used."
msgstr "Sive oblasti su slobodne, a plave i zelene u upotrebi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact values of each type of memory are not critical, and they change "
"regularly. When you evaluate this page, look at trends."
msgstr ""
"Tačne vrednosti za svaki tip memorije nisu presudne, i redovno se menjaju. "
"Podatke na ovoj stranici najbolje posmatrajte kroz razvoj stanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Does your computer have plenty of free space (grey areas)? If not, you can "
"increase the swap size or increase the physical memory."
msgstr ""
"Ima li na računaru dovoljno slobodnog prostora (sivih oblasti)? Ako nema, "
"možete povećati veličinu razmene ili fizičku memoriju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also, if your computer seems sluggish: is your physical memory full, and "
"does the hard drive always seem to be running? This suggests that you do not "
"have enough physical memory, and your computer is relying on the slower "
"virtual memory for commonly used data. Increasing your physical memory will "
"improve the responsiveness of your computer."
msgstr ""
"Ako vam računar deluje tromo: da li je fizička memorija puna, i da li "
"hard‑disk izgleda kao da uvek radi? Ovo ukazuje da nemate dovoljno fizičke "
"memorije, zbog čega se računar i za često korišćene podatke oslanja na "
"sporu, virtuelnu memoriju. Odzivnost računara tada možete poboljšati "
"dodavanjem više fizičke memorije."

#. Tag: title
